<font size="2"><b>Kaedo</b></font> - <font size="1">7/19/2002 at 08:22 AM</font>
<p>I am at the point that I feel like I am going to decline to go kill the next lodi or whatever, if I feel like I will have to handle loot at all.<br />
<br />
I think the next time something like that happens, I am going to be saying: look if I handle loot, we are going to /random by need on everyfuckingthing that drops.  If I am not handling loot, you better decide who is, because unless you decide in advance, Im not wasting my time.<br />
<br />
Basically, we got ninja'd because I was thinking "oh great here we go again, how are we supposed to do this?" while I should have been thinking "lock the corpse, and /2 tell me if you want shield OR eyepatch for upgrades and which one you'd like to roll for."<br />
<br />
I hate GD random too.  Look at Elbin.  Thx Lodi!  Nice Shield, Eyepatch, and Belt!  We have killed Lodi, what, 3 times? maybe 4? and Elbin has 3 loots from him.  Yeah random is sooo fair.<br />
<br />
I had an idea once... tho it would be a major pain to maintain it.  I was thinking of doing a master /random list.  Say we get everyone to do a /rand 1000.  And we keep a list in order like this.<br />
<br />
Name |  Roll  |<br />
<br />
Melee1   975  <br />
Priest1   654 <br />
Melee2   523 <br />
Caster1  319 <br />
Priest2   276 <br />
Caster2  111<br />
<br />
Every time you are awarded loot, you lose 1000 off your roll.  Every time you attend a "RAID" you get say 300 or so added to your roll.  So winning essentially puts you at the bottom of the list, while attending raids helps you rise up the list.  Basically, even if you rolled the 111, you will be sitting above someone that has not attended the last 3 raids if you have.<br />
<br />
I know this is just a points system =(  But loot sucks sooo bad anyway.  The way I see it, the system awards participation, while keeping the same people from winning ALL the time.  If needed, we can make UBBER items, say dragon haste for example, cost 2000 off your roll.  Target of opportunity raids may only cost 600 if you win a drop.  The numbers can be tweaked if they prove to be unbalanced.<br />
<br />
This kinda helps monks too... who help on raids like arena where only a FEW decent monk items drop.  They would be building points up for something that would really help them, like a Umbral bracer.<br />
<br />
Truthfully, I would not have a problem with loot at all if Bem was there to lay down the law every time.  And I am just shooting from the hip with my points idea, im not particulary attached to it.<br />
<br />
Any advice or feedback?</p>


