<font size="2"><b>Bustyn</b></font> - <font size="1">7/19/2002 at 04:44 PM</font>
<p>I think that some of this is once again what Bem said, our loot rules are only as good as we make them.  Random is only as good as we make it.  Yeah Elbin has won a random on 2 things that Lodi has dropped.  But what did we say when rolling for the belt?  If you will use it for your main and it's an upgrade, /ran now.  The belt was an upgrade for him, just as it would have been for Tanean or Leaas had they won.  What if we could instead sent Elbin a tell asking him not to roll since he had won an item on the last Lodi kill?  Since I know Elbin, I know he wouldn't have been upset at that in the least.  He wants what's fair for the guild too.  But on the other hand, if we say "roll if it will upgrade your main" and it upgrades his main, he's gonna roll.  If WE want things to turn out differently, we have to make it happen.  I don't want this to look like I'm defending Elbin.  I can't believe he has won 2 things on /ran and a quest piece either.  But I don't necessarily think it's his fault.  We told him he could roll, and /ran is random!  When I /ran I assume I will lose, since 98% of the time I do.  <img src="modules/XForum/images/smilies/wink.gif" border=0>  Elbin rolled assuming he would lose too.  But he happened to win.  Would we be this upset over this if Leaas had won one thing, Elbin had won one thing, Bustyn had won one thing, etc?  No, that "looks" more fair, and it may be because everyone gets something, but different people show up each time.  How can we pass loot out fairly so that everyone gets something eventually when we don't even know who will be available to show up for the next one?<br />
<br />
As for the points thing... you all know how I LOVE points systems!  <img src="modules/XForum/images/smilies/wink.gif" border=0>  The part I don't really understand is why do you /ran to get your first number?  Wouldn't it be easier to start everyone out with 1000pts?  or 0pts?  I guess the /ran just doesn't make sense to me.  Would people get points for coming to kill lodi?  Or only for raids that are planned like Kael, WW, Fri and Sat?  What if you get a drop that's a quest item?  Does that cost points too?  Say Dae and Leris both needed the same idol that dropped in KAel for the Tunare bracer (I know Dae already has it)  Do they spend points to get it?  Do they roll and whoever wins spends points on it? Would points count for everything?  Like what if Lluweni leads to groups to Kael and no officers are on?  Do they get points for that?  How do they award loot with no officers there to tell them what points they have?  I'm probably asking really dumb questions, but points are really confusing to me, and I'm not sure how or who would keep track of them and have them available and updated all the time.<br />
<br />
I agree, a simple solution would be less of a headache for us, but what if there isn't a simple solution?  What do we do?  Loot is just another reason why I HATE the "higher" end game.  Ahh for the simple days of exp groups and killing.  Where I was really excited to win a forest loop in a /ran in FM.  <img src="modules/XForum/images/smilies/wink.gif" border=0>  Loot, Rage, guild relations..... I find myself loggin on less and less and less.<br />
<br />
Sorry for my rambling.  Tell me what to do so I can help with a solution instead of being a problem.<br />
<br />
  </p>

