<font size="2"><b>Bemeni</b></font> - <font size="1">7/19/2002 at 07:48 PM</font>
<p>Loot issue aside for a moment, one thing here kinda bothers me. <br />
In my head, each officer acts as Leader of the Guild at several times during the course of play. Each of you should feel confident enough to make these decisions in my absence and know i will back you up regardless of if I agree or not (unless it is WAY off base - like something none of us have ever done and I dont even worry about). <br />
To the guild, I will support you and your decision - we may talk about it here, but The Guild sees us as of one mind about such things. <br />
So when you do Lodi, or any other situation like that, use the rules we have to make the decision, act on it, and we all move on. If you interrupt a rule differently than I do, great - there is an opportunity for us to clarify something for the future. <br />
I have said this before, and I truly believe it. <br />
Our loot system is a good one. The system isnt failing us, we are not using it properly.<br />
<br />
Maybe I have failed you by not supporting you as I should. <br />
Maybe I have unreasonable expectations of what each of you are comfortable doing. <br />
<br />
Yes, Loot is a pain, but I see that we are all distracted by littel loot issues and missing what's truly important here. Let's ease up on ourselves for once. If we feel someone gets too much Lodi loot, ask them in tells to not roll, if they chose to roll anyway, then we have done our part and can't force them. I certainly don't want to decide loot - let the roll do it. Is it fair? Not always - after all, its /random 100 - not /fair 100. <br />
No matter how fair we think we are being, someone always disagrees. We can't make everyone happy. <br />
A friend once told me everyone is responsible for their own happiness - you cant MAKE anyone happy or unhappy - they do it to themselves. <br />
<br />
We need to take that attitude more often - we do what we feel is right and let everyone else worry if they are happy. <br />
<br />
We let the /ran decide most loot - we just guide and decide who can /ran. <br />
<br />
This make any sense?</p>

